# Rasm Rhino Bridge

Use `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge` as the only bridge operator. Read `tools/rhino-bridge/README.md`, `tools/rhino-bridge/AGENTS.md`, root `AGENTS.md`, and `.claude/skills/cs-testing/references/bridge-runtime.md`.

## Current Routes

| Need | Route |
| --- | --- |
| Scenario runtime | `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge verify <scenario-or-glob>` |
| Project/source diagnostic | `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge check <target> [scenario]` |
| Bridge health | `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge doctor` |
| Local API truth | `uv run python -m tools.quality api doctor|path|xml|types|decompile` |
| Yak flow | `uv run python -m tools.quality bridge package|deploy|publish rasm-bridge <version>` |

## Runtime Rules

- Bridge build/check/package/verify routes run serially; one live Rhino endpoint handles one client.
- Yak `package`/`deploy`/`publish` write primary artifacts to project `bin/` — do not parallelize with other bridge commands.
- `quality static` and focused `--target` test runs isolate MSBuild scratch under `.artifacts/agents/<pid>/`.
- Default `tools.quality test run` executes VSTest then Stryker in order on the managed `Rasm` pair; Stryker uses project `obj/`/`bin/` — do not parallelize two default test runs with other dotnet gates.
- `bridge check <source.cs>` without a scenario can exit `3` as truthful unsupported runtime evidence after build proof.
- RhinoCode scenarios are diagnostics and verification, not publishing foundations.
- Do not use stale commands or concepts: `load-smoke`, `StartScriptServer`, job JSON, `tests/rhino`, or `pnpm check:cs`.

## Scenario kit

- `rasm-bridge-scenarios.mdc` owns `*.verify.csx` authoring rules.
- `Rasm.TestKit.Scenarios` is staged automatically; no `#r`, `#load`, or absolute paths.
- The durable evidence is one batched `facts={json}` marker parsed by `BridgeMarker.Scan`.
- Output JSON and captures land under `.artifacts/rhino/verify/`.

## Not For

- Pure xUnit/CsCheck specs.
- Analyzer, format, or static build failures.
- Rhino settings, template automation, or persistent startup policy beyond plugin `LoadTime.AtStartup`.
